[Crim. No. 3199. Second Appellate District, Division Two. April 26, 1939.] THE PEOPLE, Respondent, v. BERNE ELLIS, Appellant.

No appearance for Appellant.

Earl Warren, Attorney-General, and R. S. McLaughlin, Deputy Attorney-General, for Respondent.

THE COURT.

This case comes before the court on motion of the attorney-general to dismiss the appeal under section 1253 of the Penal Code upon the failure of the appellant to enter an appearance. No briefs have been filed by the appellant, no extensions of time have been requested and no appearance has been made by him.

Motion granted.
